						<div class="postbody">Sorry, ignore that thing above. This is my code:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Collide:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda Y_Pos<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;cmp #100<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;beq NOTHINGdown<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda X_Pos<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;cmp #99<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;beq NOTHINGdown</div>
<br />
<br />I know that that isn't correct by the way. I don't know how to get it to stop when it's at location 99,100 if 100 is Y and 99 is X. It of course stops at in the column where X= 99, and in the column where Y= 100. Ya know what I mean? I can't think of a better way to explain it. How do you get it so it only stops when X= 99 and Y=100?</div>

