					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">When I say and, I don't mean the actuall command. Is there some way to say only go to NOTHINGdown, if Y_Pos = 100 and X_Pos = 93?</div>
<br />
<br />Yeah.  You need to change the branch condition and/or destination of the first check.  What comes to mind for me is this:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;lda y_pos<br />&nbsp;cmp #100<br />&nbsp;bne skip<br />&nbsp;lda x_pos<br />&nbsp;cmp #93<br />&nbsp;beq NOTHINGdown<br />skip:<br /></div></div>

