			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh man, you should have seen the code for a PC sidescroller I tried to write when I was first learning C. I used fractional values for the player position and I think my "move until hit obstacle" tried every single sub-pixel position. A later version found the intercept of the movement vector. Still all major overkill; this wasn't a physics simulation that required absolute accuracy.
<br />
<br />Draw a picture and think about the minimum work necessary to find if movement is possible, and how far. Then find simplifications that don't add much more work than the minimum. Be sure to abstract the problem to only the essential details.
<br />
<br />Also, find a way to enjoy experimenting with 6502 programming techniques. It really helps to write simple debugging output routines to print a byte (or find an emulator with a good debugger), so you can write short test code and see the results.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
