			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Combining the responses already given in another way, here's my $0.02:  You obviously don't want to write custom code to detect collision between every object on every map of every level of your game.  As blargg suggests, you should try to abstract this problem so that it is more general.  This abstracted version (often called a "engine") should allow you design levels using the concept of objects, as opposed to pixels.  The key is to get the level of abstraction right.  The more abstract it is the more general your engine is, but it also becomes more difficult to implement it.  You want it abstract enough that it simplifies your design, but not so abstract that it does more than you need.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
